        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 3:03PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 257 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers and thunderstorms
along a line extending from near Lincoln east across the Big Belts
to near White Sulphur Springs. Movement was north at 25 mph. Expect
a period of rain and gusty winds to around 40 mph as this area of
precipitation arrives with isolated stronger thunderstorm cells
producing lightning, brief heavy rain and perhaps some small hail
over the mountains. This area of precipitation will reach as far
north as Augusta to Cascade to Monarch 430 PM.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
White Sulphur Springs, Cascade, Lincoln, Augusta, Wolf Creek,
Neihart, Fort Logan On The Smith River, York, Monarch, Martinsdale,
Eden, Fort Logan, Nilan Reservoir, Bean Lake, Bowmans Corner,
Marysville, Tower Rock State Park, Newlan Creek Reservoir, Craig, and
Lennep.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
